
[1]benzoic

   BENZO'IC, a. Pertaining to benzoin.

   Benzoic acid, or flowers of Benzoin, is a peculiar vegetable acid,
   obtained from Benzoin and other balsams, by sublimation or decoction.
   It is a fine light white matter in small needles; its taste pungent and
   bitterish, its odor slightly aromatic.
